ratios across six real-data benchmarks (10 seeds per cell). Values
${<}1$ indicate SPSC wins; \textbf{bold} = SPSC variant beats every
non-oracle baseline. LowOFUL/VOFUL run with their own online-PCA
subspace estimator (action-reward outer products with change-triggered
buffer reset), the strongest nonstationary adaptation we could give
to these originally-stationary algorithms.
A consistent pattern emerges: SPSC is dominated by LinUCB when
$d\approx r$ (top of each block), and progressively wins as $d$ grows
relative to $r$. Subspace-oblivious competitors (LinUCB, SW-LinUCB,
D-LinUCB, Restart-LinUCB, LinTS, SW-LinTS) have regret independent of
$r$, so within each $d$-block their values are identical across rows.}
